			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	The ZipZap team is building the world&#39;s premier global cash payment network, enabling consumers around the world to make purchases online by paying cash at a local retail location. We&#39;re searching for a talented User Interface designer with a healthy respect for crafting beautiful user experiences to join our small but bustling team and change the way the world transacts online.</p>
<p>
	We are a pre-launch, VC-funded startup looking to do big things in the payments space and have a great location in the heart of San Francisco&#39;s SoMa/Financial District around the corner from the Embarcadero BART station and convenient to the Ferry Building and Montgomery St stations.</p>
<p>
	This is a great opportunity for you to work directly with our Head of Product and curate an interface and experience that will touch consumers around the world.</p>
<p>
	<strong>What we offer</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		The flexibility to make your mark by working on the product experience from start-to-finish.</li>
	<li>
		Great autononimity and creative freedom, coupled with the support of a team dedicated to helping you succeed.</li>
	<li>
		An exciting new product in a space that is ripe for innovation.</li>
	<li>
		Shiny tools to get the job done.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>What you offer</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Experience crafting beautiful designs with a focus on perfecting every pixel; a resume is relative - we&#39;re more interested in seeing that you&#39;ve got the chops to pull it off.</li>
	<li>
		The ability to relate to anyone who may use our product and build an experience that is elegant, intuitive and enjoyable.</li>
	<li>
		A belief that the job is never done leading to a constant desire to iterate and improve upon your previous work.</li>
	<li>
		Strive to bring the user joy in every interaction.</li>
	<li>
		Firm grasp of HTML, CSS, and applicable programming languages.</li>
	<li>
		A portfolio that speaks for itself!</li>
</ul>
<p>
	<strong>Extra credit</strong></p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Versatile enough to do print as well as web design.</li>
	<li>
